com.blukii.sdk.info

Class InfoData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.blukii.sdk.info.InfoData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable

    public final class InfoData
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable

    Read only data object for blukii output data retrieved from blukii Manager Info CMS.

    It contains the results of the BlukiiInfo.getInfoData(List, BlukiiInfo.OnGetInfoDataListener) request to the blukii Manager Info CMS(https://manager.blukii.com).
    The InfoData fields contain the values of one corresponding blukii number.

    See Also:
    BlukiiInfo.getInfoData(List, BlukiiInfo.OnGetInfoDataListener)

      • getLanguage

        public java.lang.String getLanguage()
        Gets the output language of the InfoData set.

        It shows the language setting of the blukii number fields getUrl() and getTitle(), for OutputType.PDF also of getUrlExtra() and getPlainTextExtra().

        The value can be one of the following language codes: en-gb, fr-fr or de-de
        Returns:
        language code of the output language
        See Also:
        BlukiiInfo.getLanguagePriority()

      • getRssi

        public short getRssi()
        Gets the value of the blukii number field Visibility range.

        This value contains a Bluetooth module defined value for the rssi range in addition to the global rssi setting (see DiscoverySettings.getRssiThreshold().

        It does not affect the BLE scan itself but is designed for a better output handling.
        Returns:
        Value of blukii number field Visibility range
        See Also:
        DiscoverySettings.getRssiThreshold()

      • getTitle

        public java.lang.String getTitle()

        The language is defined by property getLanguage().

        Note: if the language specific field Title is not set getTitle contains the value of field Name (as fallback).
        Returns:

      • getUrl

        public java.lang.String getUrl()
        Gets the value of the language specific blukii number field URL.

        The language is defined by property getLanguage().

        Note: In most cases getUrl returns an url to a OutputType specific file. Exceptions is OutputType OutputType.MESSAGE: The message text itself will be returned.
Returns:
